                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="13491563" author="pkolaczk" created="Tue, 6 Nov 2012 15:59:35 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Attaching a patch fixing paged column iteration.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13491568" author="jbellis" created="Tue, 6 Nov 2012 16:05:45 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Is there a dtest for this?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13491614" author="brandon.williams" created="Tue, 6 Nov 2012 16:58:41 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;There&apos;s a wide row test and a range slice test, but not a combination of the two.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13495670" author="jbellis" created="Mon, 12 Nov 2012 22:00:24 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;committed, and create &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/riptano/cassandra-dtest/issues/5&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/riptano/cassandra-dtest/issues/5&lt;/a&gt; to follow up w/ dtest.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13500923" author="slebresne" created="Tue, 20 Nov 2012 08:49:34 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I note for the testing part that this only concern getRangeSlice with the isPaging option (i.e. for thrift, get_paged_slice) and that currently CQL never calls that so this is not reproducible with CQL. We may end up using the isPaging thing in CQL with &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-4851&quot; title=&quot;CQL3: improve support for paginating over composites&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;CASSANDRA-4851&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;CASSANDRA-4851&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; however.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13504895" author="tpatterson" created="Tue, 27 Nov 2012 20:00:27 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Just added wide_slice_test to putget_test.py in the dtests.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
